On Saturday congregants were gathered at the Reigners Bible Church in Uyo where their pastor was being ordained. JOHANNESBURG - The death toll after the roof of a church in southern Nigeria caved in has now risen to at least 100 people.On Saturday congregants were gathered at the Reigners Bible Church in Uyo where their pastor was being ordained.Construction workers of the building were allegedly rushed to finish the structure in time for the church ceremony.One eyewitness says she heard a loud bang and initially thought it was raining outside. Everybody was seated and I heard a sound, I thought it was rain. It was right at the centre. The badly injured were taken to hospital 